\f0\b\fs24 \cf0 Scalability \f1\b0\fs20 \ \pard\pardeftab720\sa320\qj \cf0 Equalizer implements a wide range of algorithms to parallelize the rendering of large data sets. Multiple graphic cards, processors and computers can be combined to render a single view. The Equalizer server distributes the rendering task across the available resources (decomposition) and assembles the results on the final view (recomposition).\ For the task decomposition, Equalizer currently supports sort-first (2D), sort-last (DB) and stereo (Eye) compounds. Time-multiplex (DPlex) is planned.\ Equalizer supports virtually any recomposition algorithm, for example binary swap or direct send for sort-last, and tile gathering for sort-first rendering.}
